sentences: Thomas Winther Andersen (born 29 April 1969) is a Norwegian-born, now Amsterdam-based jazz bassist, married to jazz singer Henriette Andersen.
He graduated from Amsterdam Conservatory 1993 and supplemented with a master at the Conservatory of Den Hague 1994.
He graduated from Amsterdam Conservatory 1993 and supplemented with a master at the Conservatory of Den Hague 1994.
In 1995 he received a grant from the Dutch foundation "Fonds Podiumkunsten", for the continuation of his studies in New York under guidance of Sal Mosca.

His compositions were recorded for the Norwegian and Dutch radio and many of them are recorded on CD like his solo album Too Much Bass?
